text: ...and our communities gets done. #NoBillNoBreak
I want a chance to go home and tell my community that I voted on a bill to demand that my and your fundamental right to be safe in our homes
So when we talk about our fundamental rights, we have a fundamental right to be safe in our own communities.
…who should not have access to a firearm.
…the police officers to get the perpetrators, who soon after, Officer Daniel Webster, was gunned down by an individual, a felon…
I don’t want to have to say any more to the parents of Lilly Garcia, or to the men and women who fought hard…
In the last 11 years, 2,000 people who are suspects on the FBI terrorist list have purchased guns. 2,000!
…on a highway by gun violence that makes absolutely no sense and has no place in our communities.
…And like all of you here today, it’s personal to me. Just last October, a 4-year-old, Lilly Garcia, was shot in her car seat…
…to make a difference for the people that I care about in my district, and in my state, and in my state, and in my country.
…that it’s not an organic process, that we don’t debate...
…and then do something about it. And when I got home, but for today, I talk about how that doesn’t happen…
…and would talk about what’s important, and that they would bring home the positive and the not so positive, examples from their districts…
I thought every single day I would be motivated and moved by my colleagues and members who would speak from their heart... #NoBillNoBreak
When I got elected to Congress, this is what I thought it was going to be like. #NoBillNoBreak https://t.co/6FWHrDeEtu

text: Americans deserve this debate. In spite of our progress, people have significant concerns and problems. #ACAforum
I want to create a caucus that focuses on payment structures. #ACAforum
I appreciate the earnest discussion about #ACA and love that I have take-away ideas. #ACAforum
I think we're doing a little better on alternative medicine. But there's no parity. We chase those reimbursements. #ACAforum
Audience statement: Insurance companies call the shots. That's the problem. Taxation without representation. #ACAforum
Provider @ #ACAforum says he is under pressure to see patients in short amount of time. Seeing progress toward emphasis on quality #ACAforum
I don't understand it, either. We need to treat the whole person. #ACAforum
Q: Why can't a physician treat the patient as an entire system rather than individual diseases? #ACAforum
I am interested in re-investing in mental health parity. I will take the @abqchamber idea back to Congress as an option.
@abqchamber is exploring solutions for behavioral health crisis in #NM Successful states have created a regional authority.
I appreciate insurance reps participating in tonight's #ACAforum http://t.co/NLRW3p7s6h
#1 call I get from constituents is about care coordination and gaps in that care. #ACAforum
#NM doesn't have enough behavioral health providers. #ACAforum
State's Centennial Care is doing universal assessments. But they aren't always timely and not always effective. #ACAforum
Q: Care coordination for mental health isn't working out. #ACAforum
#NM has limited options for health insurance coverage. Stresses the system and doesn't meet needs of residents. #ACAforum
Shift tax credit requirement so it's more reasonable. We need fewer burdens for small businesses. #ACAforum
Subsidies for small business are limited and tax credits are difficult to get. I'm not sure the penalties make sense. #ACAforum
Q: Increased costs for businesses. What can be done? #ACAforum
We lack an infrastructure for universal public healthcare system. We need more investment in public health. #ACAforum
Q: Unethical to make profit from a person's pain. Any policies to take profits out of the system? #ACAforum
We have to negotiate drug prices and hold companies accountable. Hard part is we don't want to curb research. #ACAforum
Patient responsibility is also part of the solution. But difficult to achieve. We must address it to cut costs. #ACAforum
More than 3 million Americans have chronic Hepatitis C and require expensive drugs. #ACAforum
Drug companies shouldn't be able to charge more in the US than it does for generic drugs overseas. #ACAforum
Q: Pharmaceutical costs. Breakthrough treatments less meaningful if they are not accessible to broader population. #ACAforum
I agree with Jim Hinton. Healthcare changes too often, which makes the system far too complicated. #ACAforum
Q Medicare billing rates. Jim Hinton of Presbyterian says they have too many people working to comply with regulations. #ACAforum
Patients deserve security. When health declines, that costs us all more money. #ACAforum
Pre-authorizations -- Easy with some insurance companies, but others have made it very arduous. #ACAforum
We ought to go after fraud, but sometimes we go too far. Fear of fraud is preventing some services for consumers. #ACAforum
Prosthesis technology is expensive, but critical. This is partially an audit issue, and can be very subjective. #ACAforum
Q: Tough time getting prosthetic leg. Why? #ACAforum
Q about generic drugs. Top bipartisan issue for Congress is cost of drugs, including generic drugs. Should see specific proposals. #ACAforum
Will introduce legislation to get a handle on identifying real healthcare costs. Need more transparency. #ACAforum
Programs exists to help Medicare recipients. Call my office if you need help navigating those programs. 505-346-6781 #ACAforum
This affects my mom. Without support from me, she couldn't afford Medicare co-pays.
Q3 Medicare payments have increased. Any help from #ACA? Co-pay is still 20% but as costs of care go up, so does cost-sharing. #ACAforum
In states like #NM, we still have people who are really sick and can't afford these huge barriers. That population is going to get sicker.
Q2: insurance too expensive. Some subsidies, but out-of-pocket costs are high. Insurers are shifting costs. #ACAforum
Q1 on debt related to #ACA. Goal is to reduce costs of chronic care, pharmaceutical and expensive procedures. #ACAforum
We don't have a stable and vibrant health insurance industry in #NM which limits competition. #ACAforum
#ACA didn't do enough to rein in insurance companies. #ACAforum
Downside of #ACA in #NM: Costs for many individual New Mexicans are too high. #ACAforum
The price of healthcare has been held to its slowest growth in 50 years #ACAforum
More than 16 million uninsured Americans have gained coverage so far. #ACAforum
#ACA successes in #NM: 26,000 young adults can stay on their parents' health plans until age 26. #ACAforum
You care hear the @ABQJournal Health Care forum live now on KANW -...

We must identify ways Congress can help prevent wildfires, improve the way we respond, and assist communities with post-fire recovery
A company in my district has developed larger planes or tankers that can deliver four times more retardant than any other tanker employed.
We should be looking at innovative and more cost-efficient ways to suppress fires.
The cycle of “fire borrowing” is not working and is contributing to more fires. We must stop diverting funds from fire-preventing programs.
These are real problems that must be addressed and are threatening to devastate many parts of my state and district.
NM, like many other states in the SW, experienced record-breaking fires that burned hundreds of thousands of acres.
I’m looking forward to discussing the impact that wildfires and drought have had, and will continue to have, on forests in the Southwest.
Protecting and improving the management of our forests are top priorities for me and many of the communities in my district.
